    "created_at": "2015-04-02T18:31:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-02T18:32:12Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Well... so much for the context:\nSpy disguising was not implemented in the original RA (the spy was always seen by the enemy as one of their rifle infantry), the first time it appeared was in RA2. You could disguise a spy as a dog, cow, bear, 'gator or any other critter (and, funny enough, the spy-as-a-dog seemed to move as fast as a real dog did!). I don't remember if they fixed it in Yuri's Revenge, but it's definitely repaired in an YR's total conversion mod called Mental Omega. \n\nAs for me, I'd fix it and let spies disguise as human troops only (except for hero units - Tanya and Volkov, provided that he makes it into OpenRA).\n"
  },
